                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/608½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by Mr. Hugh S. Gibson, Division of Foreign
                        Intelligence, Department of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 5, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>When the Chinese Minister called on the Secretary this morning he was handed
                    copies of the notes exchanged with the Japanese Special Ambassador. The
                    Secretary informed him that China had not been informed in regard to the
                    negotiations in progress because it was felt that if she were informed and made
                    no protest her responsibility would be engaged.</p>
            </div>
